If you do:

cpp
Copy
Edit
cout << "Enter a value:";
Nothing forces that message to immediately appear on the screen. It might just sit in the buffer until:

You add a newline (\n)

Or use endl (which adds a newline and flushes)

Or the buffer fills up

Or the program ends
